	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One of the cool things about this cape is that you don't waste any money on it.  If you hang out in BlackBurrow, you're going to come across the patches of gnoll fur whether you kill the gnoll or not - most people discard them since they're worth just a few copper.  You don't need to buy patterns to make this - just get a large sewing kit and put 4 patches together.  That's it!  It's a great way to raise your tailoring skill.<BR>
<BR>
I just made the cape with my lvl 14 necromancer with a level 21 tailoring skill.  I didn't waste a whole lot of fur with this character.  I found the best way to do this is to collect patches of gnoll fur and sew them into the gnoll fur patches.  The naming there sucks.  The &quot;patch of gnoll fur&quot; is what the gnolls drop and you sew 4 of them into a &quot;gnoll fur patch&quot;.  Do this over and over and over and over and over and over again until that becomes trivial - I think around level 20.  Once you have done that, you will be good enough to put 4 of those into the patch quarters without screwing up.  Then you can take the patch quarters and make the cape without wasting any more.  <BR>
<BR>
Don't trust me on that, because I have a pretty high WIS and INT rating so maybe that's why it was so easy.<BR>
<BR>
If you try to make it all at once you will probably waste hundreds of patches and get real aggravated - I did that with my barbarian warrior and it was a huge waste of time and money.  I ended up wasting fur 16 or 64 at a time rather than just 4 at a time.  Now my necro has 2 capes after wasting about 60 or so patches, when my warrior has zero capes and wasted hundreds of patches.<BR>
<BR>
I'm kind of bummed that it's only worth a few gold to the merchants.  I thought since it requires some skill they would pay more for it.  I'm gonna try selling it to a rogue since the Wolves of the North love us necros so much :P<BR>
<BR>
Beekonen<BR>
Level 14 Erudite Necromancer<BR>
Xegony Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
